The methodology for the ovicidal activity was followed by Su and Mulla (1998) with slight modification. Total of 100 eggs of Ae. aegypti and Ae. albopictus were immersed in 6 trays. 5 trays filled with methanolic A. pinnata extracts at different concentrations; 1500 ppm, 1000 ppm, 500 ppm, 250 ppm and 125 ppm. Control cup was filled with distilled water. The test was conducted in 5 replicates for each concentration. After treatment, the eggs from each treatment were counted under microscope and transferred into distilled water cup for hatching assessments. The percentage of eggs mortality was calculated based on the non-hatchability of eggs with unopened opercula. The hatch rates were assessed by 48 h post-treatment using formula by Govindarajan (2011);\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
